14:20.994 --> 14:22.029
But I could.

14:38.445 --> 14:39.480
Heads,

14:40.914 --> 14:41.984
I go.

14:43.450 --> 14:44.861
Tails,

14:46.119 --> 14:47.154
I don't.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.440
We're gonna get to see
the whole country, Ellie.

15:02.636 --> 15:05.038
- Gosh, I love America.
- You've never even been out of Manteca,

15:05.138 --> 15:07.982
and New York's a metropolis.
And you can't drive.

15:08.275 --> 15:11.078
Yeah, I can. My mom was a feminist.
She taught me early.

15:11.178 --> 15:13.180
Yeah, her mom's a feminist,
and I'm gonna be one, too.

15:13.280 --> 15:15.115
You don't even know what that means.

15:15.215 --> 15:18.251
It means you're gonna stay home
and take care of the Little Elvis, Billy!

15:18.351 --> 15:21.054
Do you think she's gonna make us
recite the pledge of allegiance?

15:21.154 --> 15:22.292
Maybe.

15:23.557 --> 15:25.935
She wrote to you.
Why can't you be satisfied with that?

15:26.259 --> 15:28.962
We should go visit my Aunt Daisy
in Las Vegas.

15:29.062 --> 15:32.566
And I also want to stop by the actor studio
to give that Lee Strasberg a holler.

15:32.966 --> 15:34.935
- Who's Lee Strasberg?
- Wait, who's Aunt Daisy?

15:35.035 --> 15:36.639
I got a picture of her right here.

15:37.404 --> 15:39.706
- What happened to her head?
- Little Elvis ate her face off.

15:39.806 --> 15:43.043
She's really cool. She's a showgirl
and she has her own theater on the strip.

15:43.143 --> 15:45.078
This is gonna be so boss.

15:45.178 --> 15:47.080
